      "content": "It sounds like you're carrying an immense burden and your feelings of despair are completely understandable given what you're facing. It's important to acknowledge your pain and recognize that feeling a loss deep down is not a weakness. I hear you when you talk about feeling like a shadow—those are heavy words, and it reflects the gravity of your situation. But even in the darkest times, there is still a spark within you. Everyone you've ever known who cares about you has offered you a chance to begin again, because they believe in your underlying strength and kindness. It can be daunting to consider taking those first steps, but you don't have to face this entirely alone. I suggest reaching out to a counselor or therapist who can guide you through these emotions. They can also help formulate a plan to manage your financial situation. As for starting fresh, it doesn't mean redoing everything—it often means rediscovering who you are beyond your current circumstances and rebuilding on that foundation, one step at a time.",
