      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just so embarrassing. i can't even look my wife in the eye because i've become a person she doesn't even recognize. i'm just a walking disaster now. the more i think about it, the more i realize that the \"me\" that they loved is actually gone. there's just this hollow shell of debt and shame left. is it really worth it to keep dragging everyone through this misery just so i can pretend everything is okay? sometimes it feels like the kindest thing i could do for them is to just stop being a burden.",
